#include <iostream>
#include <string>
#include <set>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    string s;
    int k, tmp, maxcount = 0;
    cin >> s >> k;
    int s_len = (int)s.size();
    for (int i = 0; i < 26; ++i)
    {
        tmp = 0;
        set<char> sst;
        for (int j = 0; j < s_len; ++j)
        {
            if (s[j] == (char)(65 + i))
            {
                tmp++;
                sst.insert(s[j]);
            }
        }
        if (tmp > 0)
            maxcount += tmp;
        else
            maxcount += s_len;
    }
    if (k < maxcount)
    {
        cout << "impossible";
    }
    else
    {
        cout << s_len - maxcount + k;
    }
    return 0;
}

```
### Explanation:
1. First line is input, read in the two parameters, s and k.
2. S is first translated into a set and then into a vector.
3. Two variables, tmp and maxcount, are initialized to 0.
4. A for loop is used to calculate the minimum number of characters.
5. If a character in s is equal to the character in the corresponding position in the sst set, then tmp is increased by 1. 
6. If a character does not appear in sst, sst is inserted.
7. If there is more than one character in the sst set, then maxcount is increased by the length of the string.
8. The number of characters is printed.
### Attention:
You can use the function (s.empty()||s.size()>1000) for detecting the input string is empty or the length of the input string is greater than 1000. If the input string is empty or the length of the input string is greater than 1000, print the word "impossible".

