This solution is based on the problem description that Polycarpus wants to cut the ribbon in a way that fulfils two conditions: each piece should have length a, b, or c, and the number of pieces is maximum. 

The first condition is the problem of finding the maximum number of pieces of the desired length. This is done using the following conditions:

1. If n is divisible by a, b, or c, then n / a, n / b, or n / c is the maximum number of pieces.
2. Otherwise, it is enough to divide the ribbon into m groups, each consisting of a + b + c pieces, and the answer will be the maximum of the number of pieces of the first group, the number of pieces of the second group, …, the number of pieces of the last group (where m is an integer).
The second condition is checked separately for each possible piece length a, b, or c.

