### My Thoughts:
Firstly, the problem asks us to find 3 different lengths so that the first length and sum of the lengths of the other 2 lengths are equal. One way to do this is brute force. Loop through the length array and check for two elements that are equal to the first element and a third element that when added to it gives the value of the first element. If any combination of three numbers is found, the function exits. If the function ends without finding any solution, print -1.
Secondly, when the length of the array is greater than 3, brute force becomes extremely difficult. To make it easier, let's sort the array and find if there are any triplets that are equal to each other and sum to each other. If any such triplet is found, the function exits.
### Explanation:
We take input from the user as an integer n and an array of length n which contains the lengths of the different worms. We sort the array and then traverse through it.
If the index of the element is 0, we simply print -1 and exit the function as the problem doesn't ask us to return any values when there is no such triplet found.
Otherwise, we traverse through the array till we reach the end. Then, we traverse again till we reach the end but this time starting from the second index. Again we traverse again till we reach the end starting from the third index.
If any combination of the indices is a triplet that adds up to the first index value, we print them and exit the function. If the function ends without finding any solution, we print -1.

