### Description:
Vasya wants to buy a pair of shoes, but he can only afford to spend money on one of them. He has spent m dollars on the left one. He wants to spend no more money than m dollars. The total cost of the second pair of shoes is s dollars. Vasya is willing to spend any amount between 0 and m dollars on the second pair. What is the maximum total cost, Vasya can spend in order to buy two pairs of shoes that together cost a total of x?
### Input
The first line of the input contains a single integer t (1 ≤ t ≤ 10) — the number of test cases. The description of the test cases follows.
The only line of each test case contains two space-separated integers m and s (0 ≤ m ≤ s ≤ 1000).
### Output
For each test case print a single integer — the maximum total cost, Vasya can spend in order to buy two pairs of shoes that together cost a total of x.
### Sample Input
3
0 1
1 1
1000 1000
### Sample Output
0
1
999
