### Explanation
For the first test case Vasya needs to buy one pair of shoes and one pair of shoes that costs a total of 1 dollar, so he can afford the shoes and therefore answer is 0.
For the second test case Vasya needs to spend money on the second pair of shoes, but it is impossible, so he will not buy any shoes.
For the third test case Vasya needs to spend no more than 999 dollars to buy one pair of shoes that costs 1 dollar and another pair of shoes that costs 999 dollars.

